==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isodulcite
<hw>I`so*dul"cite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets>
+ <ets>dulcite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white,
crystalline, sugarlike substance, obtained by the decomposition of
certain glucosides, and intermediate in nature between the hexacid
alcohols (<xex>dulcite</xex>, <xex>mannite</xex>, etc.) and the
glucoses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isodynamic</ent>⟦br⟧
